Japan money policy may change in mid - 97 - executive . The chairman of the Japan Association of Corporate Executives , Jiro Ushio , said he feels there is a possibility that Japan ' s easy monetary policy may change towards the middle of the year , a spokesman for the association said on Tuesday . " The effect of the rise in the consumption tax is relatively small , and the yen is falling versus the dollar in the foreign exchange markets due to a rise in U . S . interest rates . I think there will be new developments regarding interest rates in the future , " Ushio was quoted as telling reporters at a news conference . Ushio added that although he did not think there would be any immediate moves in interest rates , he wanted to keep a close watch on economic conditions in the April - June period . - - Tokyo Treasury Desk , + 81 - 3 - 5473 - 3748 
